<TITLE> Trader killed in Savar, 2 wives held </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Savar, Aug 15 (bdnews24.com)Police said a man who was murdered in Sripur on Saturday may have been killed for control of the lease of two public toilets, and his two wives have been arrested in connection with the killing. "Abul Kalam Azad, 45, died of knife wounds inflicted by unidentified assailants at his home while he was with his second wife, Aklima Akhter," sub-inspector of Ashulia Police Station Abdus Sattar told bdnews24.com. Azad was a fish trader in the Baipail area and the leaseholder of two public toilets in Nabinagar and Baipail. Sattar said one of the victim's two wives might have been involved with the murder. Neighbours quoted Aklima as saying an unknown person called her husband to the door at around five in the morning to give a fish order. When he answered the door four men entered the room and stabbed him, they said. She said she could not identify any of the killers in the dark, the locals reported. bdn
